implements Function4Async<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4,​R>
    An adapter that converts a conventional Function4 to an Function4Async. All asynchronous calls are executed in another thread and forwarded to the Function4.apply(Object, Object, Object, Object) method. The Executor to use for the asynchronous invocations can be chosen during creation of this adapter. If no explicit executor is given the a default executor is used. The default executor can be set using the AsyncExecutor.setDefaultExecutor(Executor) property or is created automatically by the AsyncExecutor.
    Author:
    tilmann

        Asynchronously invoke this Function4Async with the given parameter value, callback and asyncState.

        Associated with each call to beginInvoke is a FunctionAsyncResult instance returned by the call and given to the callback that can be used to track the status and outcome of the invocation.

        Specified by:
        beginApply in interface Function4Async<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4,​R>
        Parameters:
        callback - the Consumer, if given to beginInvoke, is invoked upon completion of the Function4Async's invocation and receives the same FunctionAsyncResult that is returned by the call to beginInvoke.
        asyncState - the asyncState is an arbitrary reference that, if given to beginInvoke, can be retrieved from this invocations FunctionAsyncResult.getAsyncState()
        parameter1 - the first parameter's value for the invocation
        parameter2 - the second parameter's value for the invocation
        parameter3 - the third parameter's value for the invocation
        parameter4 - the fourth parameter's value for the invocation
        Returns:
        the FunctionAsyncResult associated with this asynchronous invocation
